TASK.DESCRIPTION: This will delete the L5 flag file each night at 12:05. This flag is only needed by L5 once a month when they run their monthend. They get a flag first from the trains monthend process and then check for our flag. The Informatica server is hard coded because we can't use server variables in a command task in the current version of Informatica (7.1.5). If this changes in a future release, we should use $PMRootDir for the start of the path (replacing \\HQOLYMAPPIM1P\informatica\PowerCenter Server). If we change our Informatica server name, we will have to manually repoint to the new server.

ATTRIBUTE.VALUE: SELECT pmf.ProgramPhaseID as ProgramPhaseID, pmf.WorkPhaseID as WorkPhaseID, pmf.FundSourceID as FundSourceID, pmf.ProgramID as ProgramID, pmf.WorkItemRouteID as WorkItemRouteID, pmf.ProgramStatusId as ProgramStatusId, pmf.ApprovalCodeID as ApprovalCodeID, pmf.FundStageID as FundStageID, pmf.EstimateStageID as EstimateStageID, pmf.CountiesID as CountiesID, pmf.LegDistrictID as LegDistrictID, pmf.ProgramItemWorkItemPhaseID as ProgramItemWorkItemPhaseID, pmf.ProgramItemWorkItemID as ProgramItemWorkItemID, pmf.CurrentDolr as CurrentDolr, pmf.OriginalDolr as OriginalDolr, pmf.AuthDolr as AuthDolr, pmf.UnauthDolr as UnauthDolr, pmf.FederalDolr as FederalDolr, pmf.StateDolr as StateDolr, pmf.BondDolr as BondDolr, pmf.LocalDolr as LocalDolr, pmf.ActualDolr as ActualDolr, pmf.UnpostedActualDolr as UnpostedActualDolr, pmf.PriorAgingDolr as PriorAgingDolr, pmf.PriorAgingAuthDolr as PriorAgingAuthDolr, pmf.PriorAgingUnauthDolr as PriorAgingUnauthDolr, pmf.ActualOSCWrkHrs as ActualOSCWrkHrs, pmf.ActualRegionWrkHrs as ActualRegionWrkHrs, pmf.UnpostedActualOSCWrkhr as UnpostedActualOSCWrkhr, pmf.UnpostedActualRegioWrkHrs as UnpostedActualRegioWrkHrs, pmf.LegProjID as LegProjID, pmf.CongressDistrictID as CongressDistrictID, pmf.ProgramItemID as ProgramItemID, pmf.WorkItemID as WorkItemID, pmf.PhaseID as PhaseID, pmf.FinanceCodeID as FinanceCodeID, pmf.DateID as DateID, pmf.CapitalProgramVolumeID as CapitalProgramVolumeID, pmf.WarehouseLoadDate as WarehouseLoadDate FROM ProgramManagementFact pmf JOIN StagingCPMS..stgVolume sv ON sv.CapitalProgramVolumeID = pmf.CapitalProgramVolumeID WHERE sv.VolumeID = 1

TASKINSTANCE.NAME: EventWait

TASKINSTANCE.DESCRIPTION: This will delete the L5 flag file each night at 12:05. This flag is only needed by L5 once a month when they run their monthend. They get a flag first from the trains monthend process and then check for our flag. The Informatica server is hard coded because we can't use server variables in a command task in the current version of Informatica (7.1.5). If this changes in a future release, we should use $PMRootDir for the start of the path (replacing \\HQOLYMAPPIM1P\informatica\PowerCenter Server). If we change our Informatica server name, we will have to manually repoint to the new server.
TASKINSTANCE.NAME: DeleteL5Flag
